.TH SUITEY.SH 1 "2024" "Suitey Project Scanner"
.SH NAME
suitey.sh \- Scan project directories for test frameworks and discover test suites
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B suitey.sh
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIPROJECT_ROOT\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Suitey Project Scanner automatically detects test frameworks (BATS, Rust) in a
project directory and discovers all available test suites. It outputs structured
information about detected frameworks and discovered test suites.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
\fIPROJECT_ROOT\fR
Optional path to project root directory to scan. Defaults to current directory
if not specified.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Scan current directory:
.RS
.B suitey.sh
.RE
.PP
Scan a specific project directory:
.RS
.B suitey.sh /path/to/project
.RE
.PP
Show help:
.RS
.B suitey.sh --help
.RE
.SH DETECTED FRAMEWORKS
.SS BATS
Detects .bats files in common test directories:
.RS
.IP \(bu 4
tests/bats/
.IP \(bu 4
test/bats/
.IP \(bu 4
tests/
.IP \(bu 4
test/
.IP \(bu 4
Project root
.RE
.SS Rust
Detects Rust projects with:
.RS
.IP \(bu 4
Cargo.toml in project root
.IP \(bu 4
Test files in src/ (with #[cfg(test)] mods)
.IP \(bu 4
Test files in tests/ directory
.RE
.SH OUTPUT
The scanner outputs:
.RS
.IP \(bu 4
Detected test frameworks
.IP \(bu 4
Discovered test suites with:
.RS
.IP \(bu 4
Suite name
.IP \(bu 4
File path (relative to project root)
.IP \(bu 4
Test count
.RE
.IP \(bu 4
Warnings if framework tools are missing
.RE
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
.B 0
Success - test suites found
.TP
.B 2
Error - no test frameworks or suites detected
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR SPEC.md (5),
.BR SPEC-PROJECT-SCANNER.md (5)


